               <p>JOHN WATSON. I am a <rs id="t18270531-317-viclabel1705" type="occupation">linen-draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-317-victim1712 t18270531-317-viclabel1705"></join>, and live on Holborn-hill. On the 28th of April, about nine o'clock in the evening I was between <placeName id="t18270531-317-crimeloc1706">Brook-street, Holborn</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-317-crimeloc1706" type="placeName" value="Brook-street, Holborn"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-317-crimeloc1706" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-317-off1703 t18270531-317-crimeloc1706"></join> and <placeName id="t18270531-317-crimeloc1707">Gray's-inn-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-317-crimeloc1707" type="placeName" value="Gray's-inn-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270531-317-crimeloc1707" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270531-317-off1703 t18270531-317-crimeloc1707"></join>; I was walking along, and as I frequently do, I put my hand slightly to my pocket, and found I had no handkerchief - I was not more than two hundred yards from home - I had it when I left home; the moment I missed it I turned round, and saw Clarke going away from me, about five yards from me - I pursued, and collared him. I found my handkerchief in the left breast of his jacket. I dragged him into a shop. I saw a little boy dressed like Bond near him, but a few yards from him - two officers followed me into the shop, and they brought in Bond.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270531-317-person1713">
                  WILLIAM 
                  PRITCHARD
               <interp inst="t18270531-317-person1713" type="surname" value="PRITCHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-317-person1713" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270531-317-person1713" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I saw the prosecutor in the street, about two hundred yards within the City. I had been watching the two prisoners for an hour. I saw Bond try Mr. Watson's pocket several times, without success, and just as he passed a tailor's shop by Brook-street, Bond took the handkerchief out of his pocket, and ran off directly - I pursued and took him, and found another handkerchief on him, which I had seen Clarke take from a gentleman half an hour before - they were together.</p>
               <p>CLARKE's Defence. I picked up the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>BOND - <rs id="t18270531-317-verdict1708" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18270531-317-verdict1708" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 14.</p>
